examples.en: We tumbled out into the street.
He tumbled into bed and fell asleep.
The clothes tumbled in the dryer.
The king was tumbled on the plain.
He tumbled flop into the mud.
Her long dark hair tumbled over her shoulders.
The accident tumbled the passengers out of the car.
He tried to build a house of cards but it soon tumbled over.
He tripped over a stone and tumbled.
He tripped and tumbled to the ground.
Prices tumbled after the devaluation of the currency.
It is she who has tumbled my hopes and all my pride down.
Mortgage rates tumbled to their lowest level for 25 years.
The tower of the World Trade Center tumbled after the plane hit it
Her face had been gashed by the rocks as she tumbled down the embankment.
